@remark *** KEYBOARD SHORTCUT HELP ***

@node MAIN "Keyboard Shortcuts"

@{FG Highlight}MENU COMMANDS@{FG Text}

Keyboard shortcuts for menu commands are shown in the menus. Most menu
shortcuts use the Right Amiga key, which is represented by the @{B}@{I}A
@{UB}@{UI}symbol in the menu. To use one of these shortcuts, hold down
the Right Amiga key and press the character shown in the menu.

Type menu commands followed by a caret ^ symbol and then a character can
be executed by pressing the character while holding down the Ctrl key.
Object menu commands followed by a single character can be executed by
pressing the character without holding down a qualifier key. (If the
Object menu shortcut is uppercase, Shift must be held down.)

Only Right Amiga keyboard equivalents can be shown in the menus with
AmigaDOS 2.0Ł2.1. The Type and Object menu keyboard equivalents will not
be visible although they will still function.
@{code}
@{FG Highlight}Type                          Object@{FG Text}
Style Tags            ^ Y     Style Tags       y
Attributes            ^ A     Edit             e
Font                  ^ F     Information      i
Normal                ^ N     Line/Fill        l
Bold                  ^ B     Trapping         T
Italic                ^ I     Text Wrap        w
Underline             ^ U     Text Anchor      A
Outline               ^ O     Duplicate        d
Reverse               ^ R     Transform        t
Shadow                ^ H     Rotate           r
Small Caps            ^ M     Move             M
Superscript           ^ P     Move to Page     p
Subscript             ^ S     Align            a
Heavier               ^ 1     Distribute       D
Lighter               ^ 2     Split Paths      s
Larger                ^ 3     Merge Paths      m
Smaller               ^ 4     Group            g
Line/Fill             ^ L     Ungroup          u
Tabs                  ^ T     Lock             L
Insert Soft Hyphen    ^ -     Unlock           U
Uppercase             ^ 5     Make Drawing     K
Lowercase             ^ 6     Add to Drawing   S
Capitalized           ^ 7     Dissolve Drawing W
Page #                ^ 8     Bring to Front   f
Previous Frame Page # ^ 9     Bring Forward    F
Next Frame Page #     ^ 0     Send to Back     b
                              Send Backward    B
@{body}
@{body}
@{FG Highlight}OBJECT EDITING SHORTCUTS@{FG Text}

@{FG Highlight}Nudging objects:@{FG Text} Object(s) must be selected with
the Object or Reshape tool to nudge them.
@{code}
@{U}Nudge objects@{UU}                @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Nudge left                   Left Arrow
Nudget right                 Right Arrow
Nudge up                     Up Arrow
Nudge down                   Down Arrow
* hold down a Shift key to move by 10% of the nudge amount
@{body}
@{body}
@{FG Highlight}Move and scale contents of a frame:@{FG Text} A picture,
drawing, EPS object, compound object, or group must be selected with the
Reshape tool to shift or scale the contents within its frame.
@{code}
@{U}Shift contents of frame@{UU}      @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Shift left                   Ctrl Left Arrow
Shift right                  Ctrl Right Arrow
Shift up                     Ctrl Up Arrow
Shift down                   Ctrl Down Arrow
Center contents in frame     Shift Ctrl C
* hold down a Shift key to shift by 10% of the nudge amount

@{U}Scale contents of frame@{UU}      @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Increase by 5%               Alt Up Arrow
Increase by 1%               Shift Alt Up Arrow
Decrease by 1%               Shift Alt Down Arrow
Increase by 5%               Alt Down Arrow
Scale to fit in frame        Shift Ctrl F
Scale and maintain aspect    Shift Alt F
@{body}
@{body}
@{FG Highlight}Path point editing:@{FG Text} You can edit the points in a
path with the keyboard when at least one point in a path is selected with
the Reshape tool.
@{code}
@{U}Select and delete points@{UU}     @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Select next point            Alt Up Arrow
Select previous point        Alt Down Arrow
Delete selected points       Del

@{U}Nudge points@{UU}                 @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Nudge left                   Left Arrow
Nudget right                 Right Arrow
Nudge up                     Up Arrow
Nudge down                   Down Arrow
* hold down a Shift key to move by 10% of the nudge amount
@{body}
@{body}

@{FG Highlight}TEXT EDITING SHORTCUTS@{FG Text}

@{FG Highlight}Moving the insertion point:@{FG Text} You can move the
insertion point when it has been placed into a text object with the Text
tool by using the keyboard.
@{code}
@{U}Move the insertion point to@{UU}  @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Previous character           Left Arrow
Next character               Right Arrow
Previous word                Alt Left Arrow
Next word                    Alt Right Arrow
Previous line                Up Arrow
Next line                    Down Arrow
Previous paragraph           Alt Up Arrow
Next paragraph               Alt Down Arrow
Start of line                Shift Left Arrow
End of line                  Shift Right Arrow
Start of column              Shift Up Arrow
End of column                Shift Down Arrow
Start of frame               Shift Alt Up Arrow
End of frame                 Shift Alt Down Arrow
Start of article             Ctrl Up Arrow
End of article               Ctrl Down Arrow
@{body}
@{body}
@{FG Highlight}Text selection and deletion:@{FG Text} To select text with
the keyboard, you must start a block at the insertion point, move the
insertion point with the arrow keys (see above), and end the block.
@{code}
@{U}Select text@{UU}                  @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Start block                  Ctrl W
End block                    Ctrl Q
Start an additional block    Ctrl Z

@{U}Delete text@{UU}                  @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Previous character           Backspace
Next character               Del
Selected text                Del
Previous word                Alt Backspace
Next word                    Alt Del
@{body}
@{body}
@{FG Highlight}Text Size:@{FG Text} Use these shortcuts to change the
text size.
@{code}
@{U}Set type size@{UU}                @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Increase to next listed size Shift Ctrl >
Increase by 1 pt             Alt Shift Ctrl >
Decrease by 1 pt             Alt Shift Ctrl <
Decrease to next listed size Shift Ctrl <

@{U}Set horizontal scale@{UU}         @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Increase by 5%               Shift Ctrl }
Increase by 1%               Alt Shift Ctrl }
Decrease by 1%               Alt Shift Ctrl {
Decrease by 5%               Shift Ctrl {
@{body}
@{body}
@{FG Highlight}Kerning, tracking and leading:@{FG Text} When a block of
text is selected, using the kerning and tracking shortcuts will set the
tracking. When the insertion point is between two characters, these
shortcuts will manually kern the characters.

The leading shortcuts change the leading in different amounts, depending
on whether relative or fixed leading is selected.
@{code}
@{U}Set kerning or tracking@{UU}      @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Increase by 0.05em           Ctrl ]
Increase by 0.01em           Alt Ctrl ]
Decrease by 0.01em           Alt Ctrl [
Decrease by 0.05em           Ctrl [

@{U}Set leading@{UU}                  @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Increase by 1 pt / 5%        Ctrl ;
Increase by 0.5 pt / 1%      Alt Ctrl ;
Decrease by 0.5 pt / 1%      Alt Ctrl '
Decrease by 1 pt / 5%        Ctrl '
@{body}
@{body}
@{FG Highlight}Breaks and indents:@{FG Text} You can specify where text
should be broken into paragraphs and columns with break and indent
controls. The insertion point must be placed in a text object to insert
these.
@{code}
@{U}Insert control@{UU}               @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Right indent tab             Shift Tab
Indent here                  Ctrl \
New paragraph                Return
New line                     Shift Return
Column break                 Enter
Page break                   Shift Enter

@{FG Highlight}TOOLBOX AND TOOLBAR SHORTCUTS@{FG Text}
@{body}
@{body}
Keyboard shortcuts for some toolbox and toolbar features allow you to
perform common operations without removing your hands from the keyboard.
@{code}
@{U}Function@{UU}                     @{U}Shortcut@{UU}
Next tool                    Alt Tab
Previous tool                Shift Alt Tab
Activate Edit palette        Ctrl E
Go to Page                   Ctrl G
First Page                   Shift Ctrl J
Previous Page                Ctrl J
Next Page                    Ctrl K
Last Page                    Shift Ctrl K
@{body}
@{body}
